******
[2] Cholera - Dominican Republic (San Juan Province)
Date: Thu 27 Nov 2014
Source: Noticias Sin [in Spanish, machine transl., edited]
http://www.noticiassin.com/2014/11/al-menos-trece-personas-con-sintomas-de-colera-en-san-juan/


13 people have been admitted to the hospitals of Juan de Herrera and San Juan de la Maguana related to symptoms of cholera. Of these, 6 are in the hospital of San Juan de la Maguana and 7 in the municipality of Juan de Herrera [San Juan province, Dominican Republic].

The majority come from communities of the northern area of San Juan de la Maguana [San Juan province], among these, the Maguanas, Canafistol and surrounding areas. So far the authorities have not confirmed if the diarrheal outbreaks have to do with the cholera outbreak which has affected hundreds of people in the past few years.

[Byline: Peter Pablo Mateo]

